<div type="edition" xml:lang="tam-Latn" rendition="class:tamil maturity:vernacular">

<p>
<lb n="1"/><hi rend="grantha">śrī</hi> kopparake<hi rend="grantha">sa</hi>ripaṉmaṟku yāṇṭu 10 Āvatu ciṟupaḻuvūr maṟa
<lb n="2"/>vaṉi<hi rend="grantha">śva</hi>ramuṭaiyārkku kuṉṟakūṟṟattu nāṭṭār cantirātita
<lb n="3"/>val Iravum pakalum nontāviḷakkoṉṟiṉukku ney Eri
<lb n="4"/>ya Uḻakkāka vaitta Āṭu toṇṇūṟu paṉmāye<hi rend="grantha">śvara rakṣai</hi>
</p>

</div>

<div type="apparatus">

</div>

<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>Prosperity! This is the 10th year of Kōpparakesarivarman. For the Lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uṭaiyār</foreign></supplied> of Maṟavaṉīśvaram of Ciṟupaḻuvūr, the Nāṭṭārs of Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam, for one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uḻakkāka</foreign></supplied> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ney</foreign></supplied> for one perpetual lamp <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nontāviḷakkoṉṟiṉukku</foreign></supplied> to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eriya</foreign></supplied>, as long as the sun and the moon endure, gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> ninety goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āṭu toṇṇūṟu</foreign></supplied>. This is under the protection of the Paṉmāheśvaras.</p></div>

